modules.description: Provides functions for parsing and generating GPX files, including reading track points, routes, and waypoints. Operates on custom data types representing geographic coordinates, timestamps, and elevation data. Used to convert GPS data between file formats and extract location-based information for mapping applications.

Provides boolean operations on polygon data structures using GPC (General Polygon Clipper) algorithms. Works with vertex arrays and contour-based polygon representations to construct, clip, and debug polygons. Enables precise clipping of one polygon against another using operators like union, intersection, and difference.
